# Real-time Audio

- Apply the `shadowing-development` SOP and read ADR-0004/0005.
- Use sample/render time for loop and recording boundaries.
- Keep UI refresh timers outside the real-time clock.
- Audio callbacks must not block, access SQLite, or allocate without a fixed bound.
- Handle interruption, route removal, early stop, and file-write failure explicitly.
- Commit a Take only after its temporary recording is playable and moved successfully.
